    {
      "name": "<think>\nThe user wants me to translate \"Sense Magic\" from English to zh-CN (Simplified Chinese).\n\n\"Sense Magic\" - this appears to be a game term, likely from a video game or RPG context. It could refer to:\n1. A spell/ability name - \"感知魔法\" or \"魔法感知\"\n2. A general concept - \"感知魔法\" (to sense magic)\n\nIn gaming contexts, this is typically translated as:\n- \"感知魔法\" (gǎnzhī mófǎ) - to sense/perceive magic\n- \"魔法感知\" (mófǎ gǎnzhī) - magic sensing/awareness\n\nGiven this is likely from a game item or ability name context (Domain: item.name), the most common translation would be \"感知魔法\" or \"魔法感知\".\n\nI'll go with \"感知魔法\" as it's the more natural reading when used as an item name.\n</think>\n\n感知魔法",
      "type": "feat",
      "img": "icons/svg/mystery-man.svg",
