    {
      "name": "Ruidium Corruption: When a creature is required to make a Ruidium Corruption save due to a trait or action of this nullifier, the creature must succeed on a DC 15 Charisma saving throw or suffer Ruidium Corruption",
      "type": "feat",
      "img": "icons/svg/mystery-man.svg",
      "system": {
        "description": {
          "value": "<p><think>\nThe user wants me to translate the text from English to Simplified Chinese (zh-CN). The text is:\n\n\"If the creature is already affected by Ruidium Corruption, it instead gains 1 level of exhaustion.\"\n\nThis appears to be game-related text, possibly from Dungeons & Dragons or a similar RPG system, referring to a status effect called \"Ruidium Corruption\" and \"exhaustion\" levels.\n\nLet me translate this:\n\n- \"If the creature\" = 如果该生物\n- \"is already affected by\" = 已经受到...影响\n- \"Ruidium Corruption\" = 锐毒侵蚀（或保持Ruidium Corruption不变，因为是专有名词）\n- \"it\" = 它\n- \"instead gains\" = 则改为获得\n- \"1 level of exhaustion\" = 1级力竭\n\nLet me put it together:\n如果该生物已经受到锐毒侵蚀的影响，则改为获得1级力竭。\n\nOr more naturally:\n如果该生物已受锐毒侵蚀影响，则改为获得1级力竭。\n\nActually, looking at game terminology more carefully:\n- \"Ruidium Corruption\" is likely a specific game term that might be kept as \"Ruidium Corruption\" or translated as \"锐毒侵蚀\"\n- \"exhaustion\" in D&D context is \"力竭\"\n\nI'll go with:\n如果该生物已受Ruidium Corruption影响，则改为获得1级力竭。\n\nOr fully translated:\n如果该生物已受锐毒侵蚀影响，则改为获得1级力竭。\n</think>\n\n如果该生物已受锐毒侵蚀影响，则改为获得1级力竭。</p>",
          "chat": ""
        },
